        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): avoid OpenAI realtime double greeting",
        "body": "Fixes #85846\n\n## Summary\n\n- Avoid the voice-call plugin's duplicate OpenAI realtime first greeting by folding queued outbound OpenAI initial greetings into the realtime session instructions.\n- Suppress only the explicit OpenAI on-ready `triggerGreeting()` for that queued initial greeting path, leaving OpenAI server VAD auto-response as the single first-turn response source.\n- Preserve existing OpenAI manual speech semantics: `triggerGreeting()` still creates a conversation user item and requests a response.\n- Keep non-OpenAI realtime providers on the existing explicit on-ready initial greeting path.\n- No config surface or plugin API surface changed.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 2 files, 69 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `git diff origin/main...HEAD --check`\n\nSigned head: `e0462880d9844eb34ad921d0ed3c18cce15774d1`.\n\nKnown proof gap: no live Twilio/OpenAI outbound call was run in this environment.",
